The paper deals with mining patterns in relational databases, which is a core topic in the database community (cs.DB). The focus is on recommender systems, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as rough sets and granular computing, which are common in the machine learning community (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of pattern explosion, which is a common challenge in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for rule mining, which falls under the category of computational intelligence and optimization (cs.SI).
